1) What is Kotlin? / Describe Kotlin in brief.
Kotlin is a general-purpose, statically typed, open-source programming language that runs on the JVM. It runs on JVM and can be used anywhere Java is used today. It can be compiled either using Java source code or LLVM compiler. It is generally used to develop Android apps, server-side apps, and much more.
*
Statically typed ka matlab hai ki har variable ka data type pehle se fixed hota hai aur compiler compile time par check karta hai. Agar galat type ki value di jaye, to error aa jata hai.
JVM Compiler → Jab Kotlin ka use Java ke sath ya Android app banane ke liye hota hai.
LLVM Compiler → Jab Kotlin se native applications (jaise Windows, Linux, macOS, iOS) banani hoti hain.
------------------------------------
| general purpose                  |
| statically typed                 |
|open source prog lang             |
|run by jvm                        |
------------------------------------


