7) What is the difference between the variable declaration with val and variable declaration with const?
Definition:

val ek read-only variable hota hai. Iski value sirf ek baar assign ki ja sakti hai. Ek baar value de di, to baad me usse change nahi kar sakte.

Example
val name = "Sakshi"

Yahan

name ki value "Sakshi" hai.
Agar baad me likhen
name = "Rahul"

To Error aayega.

Isliye val = one-time assignment.

Ab const kya hota hai?

Definition:

const ka matlab constant value hota hai. Matlab jis value ko kabhi bhi change nahi karna hai, uske liye const use karte hain.

Ye program compile hone se pehle hi fix ho jati hai.

Isliye ise compile-time constant bhi kehte hain.

Example

const val PI = 3.14

Ya

const val APP_NAME = "Calculator"

PI aur APP_NAME kabhi change nahi honge.

Ab confusion yahi hai...

Student puchte hain

Sir, val bhi change nahi hota aur const bhi change nahi hota. To difference kya hai?

Answer👇

val
Read-only variable hai.
Value runtime me bhi mil sakti hai.
Function se value le sakta hai.

Example

val time = System.currentTimeMillis()

Yahan time ki value program chalne par milegi.

Isliye ye const nahi ho sakta.

const
Hamesha fixed value hoti hai.
Compile time par hi value pata hoti hai.
Sirf String ya primitive values (Int, Double, Boolean, etc.) ke liye use hota hai.
Function ki return value ko const nahi bana sakte.

Example

const val MAX_USERS = 100

Ye value kabhi change nahi hogi.

Real-life Example

Socho school me do cheeze hain.

val

Tumhari Date of Birth

Ek baar set ho gayi.

Badal nahi sakte.

Lekin ye program chalne ke time bhi mil sakti hai.

const

School ka naam

ABC Public School

Ye pehle se hi fix hai.

Sab jagah same rahega.

Program chalne se pehle hi pata hai.
